====Entering a topic====

We assume that sync has been run, at least when the app was started even if background sync is off. 

On entering the topic we should do one of:
*Check if there are unread messages in the cache for this topic, if there are:
  * Ascertain the oldest unread message (some may have been read via a different app)
  * Build the onscreen thread from the cache landing on the oldest unread message.

*Check if there are any messages in the cache for this topici if there are not:
  * Get the last 30 days of messages for this topic using an API call and cache.
  * Ascertain the oldest unread message (some may have been read via a different app)
  * Get the entire thread that contains this unread message using an API call and cache.
  * Build the onscreen thread from the cache landing on the oldest unread message.

*Display the most recent thread in this topic and land on the root message

In all the above cases, check to see if there are any messages missing from the cache, and back fill the topic.
